        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Installation of Cages in Reservoirs Scheme&quot; was launched by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry &amp; Dairying, Government of India, under the umbrella scheme &quot;Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana&quot;. It aims to promote sustainable aquaculture practices by supporting cage fish farming in water bodies. Under this scheme, a grant of ₹3,00,000/- per unit to the individuals and groups for setting up cage fish farms, thereby encouraging entrepreneurship, increasing fish production, and generating employment.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Grant Amount:**\n\n- ₹3,00,000/- per unit (per cage).\n\n**Grant Proportion:**\n\n- 40% of unit cost for General Category beneficiaries.\n- 60% of unit cost for Scheduled Caste/Women beneficiaries.\n\n**Cage Limit for Assistance:**\n\n- Up to 5 cages for individual farmers.\n- Up to 20 cages for registered cooperative societies/self-help groups/joint liability groups (with at least 10 members).\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to promote cage fish farming. It provides grants per unit to the individuals and groups for sustainable aquaculture practices.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The \"Installation of Cages in Reservoirs Scheme\" was launched by the Ministry Of Fisheries, Animal Husbandry & Dairying, Government of India, under the umbrella scheme \"Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana\". It aims to promote sustainable aquaculture practices by supporting cage fish farming in water bodies. Under this scheme, a grant of ₹3,00,000/- per unit to the individuals and groups for setting up cage fish farms, thereby encouraging entrepreneurship, increasing fish production, and generating employment."
